###Mean

We want the mean of $\bar{x}_\text{A}-\bar{x}_\text{B}$:

$\begin{align}
\mu_{\bar{x}_\text{A}-\bar{x}_\text{B}}&=\blueE{\mu_\text{A}}-\maroonD{\mu_\text{B}}
\\\\
&=\blueE{57}-\maroonD{54}
\\\\
&=3
\end{align}$

Intuition check: The population means have a difference of $3$ grams, so that is the mean or expected difference in the sample means.

###Standard deviation

$\begin{align}
\sigma_{\bar{x}_\text{A}-\bar{x}_\text{B}}&=\sqrt{\dfrac{\redE{\sigma_{\text{A}}}^2}{\purpleD{n_\text{A}}}+\dfrac{\goldE{\sigma_{\text{B}}}^2}{\purpleD{n_\text{B}}}}
\\\\
&=\sqrt{\dfrac{\redE{6}^2}{\purpleD{60}}+\dfrac{\goldE{8}^2}{\purpleD{60}}}
\end{align}$

###Answer

The mean and standard deviation of the sampling distribution of $\bar{x}_\text{A}-\bar{x}_\text{B}$ are:

$\begin{align}
\mu_{\bar{x}_\text{A}-\bar{x}_\text{B}}&=3\\\\
\sigma_{\bar{x}_\text{A}-\bar{x}_\text{B}} &= \sqrt{\dfrac{6^2}{60}+\dfrac{8^2}{60}}
\end{align}$

